---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout title="Is AB a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 4 Points)" description="AB is a valid Scrabble word worth 4 points in both TWL and SOWPODS. It means an abdominal muscle (informal). Learn extensions like ABS and ABB plus strategy tips." keywords="is ab a scrabble word, ab scrabble, ab valid scrabble, ab points scrabble, two letter a words, ab meaning scrabble, abs scrabble word">
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Is AB a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 4 Points)","description":"AB is a valid Scrabble word worth 4 points in both TWL and SOWPODS. It means an abdominal muscle (informal).","datePublished":"2026-06-29","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/is-ab-a-scrabble-word"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is AB a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, AB is valid in both TWL (North American) and SOWPODS (International) Scrabble dictionaries. It scores 4 points (A=1, B=3) and means an abdominal muscle in informal usage."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What does AB mean in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"AB is an informal shortened form of 'abdominal muscle.' It's commonly used in fitness contexts (abs, six-pack abs). In Scrabble, it's a handy 2-letter word for dumping a B tile while scoring a solid 4 points."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What words can you extend AB into?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"AB extends into ABS (5pts — adding S), ABB (7pts — a type of yarn), ABLE (6pts), ABED (7pts), ABET (6pts), and many more. ABS is particularly useful as it uses the common S tile for an easy extra point."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <a href="/blog/two-letter-words/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors text-gray-300">Two-Letter Words</a>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Is AB a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 4 Points)</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-29">June 29, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>4 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Yes, AB is a valid Scrabble word worth 4 points in both TWL and SOWPODS. It's an informal term for an abdominal muscle — the same "abs" you hear about in fitness. With B worth 3 points, AB is a solid 2-letter play for offloading B while setting up extensions like ABS or ABB.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-green-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-green-950/30 to-emerald-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-green-500/70">✓ VALID</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">AB</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-green-300 font-semibold mb-3">4 points · A=1, B=3 · An abdominal muscle (informal)</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">Valid in both TWL (Tournament Word List) and SOWPODS (Collins Scrabble Words). AB is the shortened form of "abdominal" — used casually to refer to stomach muscles. One of the better 2-letter B words thanks to B's 3-point value.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">4</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Points</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">Both</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TWL + SOWPODS</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">9 A-tiles</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Available</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">2 B-tiles</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">In the Bag</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">AB Extensions: Build From It</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ABS</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">5pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ABB</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ABLE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ABED</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">7pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ABET</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ABUT</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">AB Strategy: When to Play It</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">B-dump play:</span> Only 2 B-tiles in the bag, so drawing one is common. AB gives you 4 points while clearing B from your rack. Better than holding B for a turn hoping for a longer word.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Setup for ABS:</span> Play AB, then next turn add S to make ABS (5pts). Or hook it into longer words like ABLE, ABED. The A-B combination opens many 4+ letter extensions.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Parallel plays:</span> Place AB parallel to an existing word to form crosswords. B on a DLS scores 6 from one tile. A is easy to cross with (AA, AD, AE, AG, AH, AI, AL, AM, AN, AR, AS, AT, AW, AX, AY).</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Did You Know?</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">AB is one of <span class="text-white font-medium">several valid 2-letter words starting with A</span> that use a consonant worth 3+ points: AB (4pts) and AX (9pts). This makes it a reliable A-word when you need to score while dumping a tricky consonant.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/is-ad-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is AD a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 3 Points)</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/is-bo-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is BO a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 4 Points)</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 dark:from-blue-900/20 dark:to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Check any word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up required</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
